main event: A witness reported observing an object in the sky, concluded to be Venus due to its pinkish cast and movement.
interesting points: The sighting lasted for about 15 minutes,The object was observed moving from west to east at approximately 30 degrees above the horizon,The witness indicated the object was initially seen at a distance of 4 miles and estimated its speed to be 6.8 miles per minute,The report included statements that the observer, an Air Force Weather Observer, had never seen anything like it in 12 years of observation,The sighting was reported on 3 March 1967, and there were no photographs taken.
sighted object: an object resembling the planet Venus
witness description: A 29-year-old male, Air Force Weather Observer, familiar with sky observations.
